  (6, 'If you test a drug and find p-value = 0.02, using α = 0.05, what is your conclusion?', 'The drug has no effect (Accept H0)', 'The drug has a statistically significant effect (Reject H0)', 'The study is invalid', 'Run the test again with a different mean', 'B', 2, 8),
  (6, 'A Pearson correlation coefficient (r) of –0.85 indicates a:', 'Strong positive relationship', 'Weak negative relationship', 'Strong negative relationship', 'No relationship', 'C', 2, 9),
