  (6, 'What does the Central Limit Theorem (CLT) state about the sampling distribution of the mean?', 'It will be skewed if the population is skewed', 'It approaches a normal distribution as sample size gets large, regardless of the population distribution', 'The variance increases with sample size', 'It is identical to the population distribution', 'B', 2, 12),
